    body: 'Pay **2 stress** to get **one** of these on an action roll:\n\n· **+1 die** to the pool\n· **+1 effect level** (limited → standard → great)\n· **Perform an extraordinary feat** — something at the edge of human capability, appropriate to the attribute\n\nYou choose **one**, not all three, and you may only push **once per roll**.\n\nThe experienced-player note: **+1 effect is usually the stronger buy**. An extra die improves your odds a little; an extra effect level improves your *result*, and it applies on the 4–5 you were probably going to get anyway.\n\nPushing **stacks** with a **Devil\'s Bargain** (+1d) and an **assist** (+1d), so a determined character can turn a 2d roll into 5d — at the cost of 2 stress, a complication, and an ally\'s stress.\n\nStress is not free health. Nine boxes and you take **trauma**. Push when it matters.',
