    kind: 'mechanic',
    short: 'A dice roll for a question nobody is acting on — the GM rolls to see how the uncertain world resolves.',
    body: 'A **fortune roll** answers an uncertain question when **no PC is taking an action**. How much does the fence pay? Does the rival gang notice? How far does the fire spread? Is the contact still alive?\n\nThe GM builds a pool from whatever factors apply (a faction\'s **tier**, a relevant rating, the sheer odds), rolls, and reads the highest die on the usual ladder:\n\n· **6** — a **good** result / full measure\n· **4–5** — a **mixed** result / partial measure\n· **1–3** — a **poor** result / little or nothing\n· **critical** — a **great** result\n\nBecause nobody acted, there is **no position, no effect, no stress, and nothing to resist**. It is not an action roll and it never marks XP.\n\nFortune rolls also do bookkeeping: they resolve **downtime activities**, size up **clock** progress off-screen, and answer "what does the world do while you\'re not looking".',
