    short: 'A 9-box track you spend to push, assist, flashback and resist; fill all 9 and you take Trauma.',
    body: '**Stress** is the central currency of Blades. Every PC has a **9-box** track and spends from it constantly:\n\n· **Push yourself** — **2 stress** for +1d, +1 effect, or an extraordinary feat\n· **Assist** an ally — **1 stress** for +1d\n· **Resistance roll** — **6 minus your highest die**, so **0–5 stress**\n· **Flashback** — **0, 1, or 2+ stress** depending on how much it stretches\n\nWhen you **mark the 9th box**, you take **Trauma**: choose a trauma condition, **clear your entire stress track**, and carry the scar permanently. Any excess stress from that moment is lost, not carried over.\n\nClear stress in **downtime** by **indulging your vice** — roll your **lowest attribute rating**, clear stress equal to the highest die.\n\nStress is *not* hit points. It is not damage taken; it is effort spent. A character with 8 stress is not bleeding — they are strung out, running on nerve, one hard choice from breaking. That distinction drives every table decision in the last hour of a score.',
