    kind: 'condition',
    short: 'Taken when you fill 9 stress: a permanent scar, chosen from eight. Four traumas and the character retires.',
    body: 'Fill the **9th stress box** and you take **trauma**. Choose one of the eight conditions, **clear all stress**, and mark it on your sheet. It is **permanent** — trauma never heals.\n\nThe list:\n\n· **Cold** — you are not moved by emotional appeals or social bonds\n· **Haunted** — you are obsessed with the spirit world, secrets, and the misfortune of others\n· **Obsessed** — you are single-minded about a target, activity, or fixation\n· **Paranoid** — you imagine danger everywhere; you can\'t trust others\n· **Reckless** — you have little regard for your own safety or that of others\n· **Soft** — you lose your edge; you become sentimental and passive\n· **Unstable** — your emotional state is volatile; you can instantly rage, or fall into despair, or freeze\n· **Vicious** — you seek out opportunities to hurt people, even for no reason\n\nWhen a trauma is relevant, you must **play it** — it takes the wheel. Playing your trauma is also an **XP trigger**.\n\nAt **4 traumas**, the character is **retired**: they are done, permanently, and you make a new PC. Retirement is not death; it is a broken person leaving Doskvol, which is often worse.\n\nThe warning that matters: **resisting is how you die**. Not from harm — from stress.',
